' openfiledialog
' --------------

' 'openfiledialog([file_extension])' shows a system dialog for opening an existing file. Set the
' optional string file_extension to a file extension (such as ”txt”) to only list files of that
' type. If the user selects a file, its full path is returned.
filename = openfiledialog("txt")
if filename
    pln "You selected the file " + chr(34) + filename + chr(34)
else
    pln "You didn't select any file!"
endif

system "pause"
